	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A triple murder case has been opened for investigation following a shooting at Nyanga taxi rank on Friday. "According to information the shooting incident occurred this afternoon at about 14:00," police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana told News24. "Three men in their forties were shot and fatally wounded by unidentified men who entered a meeting and fired shots [at] the victims." Provincial detectives are combing the scene for clues. More on this story as it develops.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  